IMHO, there is no good reason for {{listStatus}} to return {{null}}. It should throw IOExceptions upon errors or return empty list.

To enforce the contract that null is an invalid return, update javadoc and leverage @Nullable/@NotNull/@Nonnull annotations.

So far, I am only aware of the following functions that can return null:
* RawLocalFileSystem#listStatus

comments.body:
Thanks [~boky01], it is a dup of HADOOP-7352.

One idea is to add {{@NotNull}} to {{FileSystem#listStatus}}:
{code}
  @NotNull
  public abstract FileStatus[] listStatus(Path f) throws IOException;
{code}

Then run IntelliJ - Analyze - "Run Inspection by Name ..." - "@NotNull/@Nullible problems" (multiple times if necessary) in order to:
* Propagate {{@NotNull}} to subclasses' {{listStatus}} method
* Detect any implementation of {{listStatus}} that may return {{null}}

Patch 003:
* {{RawLocalFileSystem#listStatus}} throws ACE when a directory is not accessible
* Modify FS contract test {{testListStatusThrowsExceptionForUnreadableDir}}

